{{Refimprove|date=October 2017}}
The '''Victorian Rally Championship''' was the [[Evolution (term)|evolution]] series of [[Rallying|car rallies]] in [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria, Australia]]. Prior to 1972, car rallies/trials relied heavily on the ability of a [[navigator]] to read a [[map]] and direct their [[Driving|driver]] over a planned [[Course (navigation)|course]] covering [[shire]] [[road]]s and [[forest]] tracks at [[night]].
In 1972 the series evolved in line with the improvement of [[forest track]]s, and the [[population]] of properties along Shire roads – into a more driver-oriented [[sporting event|event]].
Route instructions became comprehensive, making it easier for a crew to avoid getting lost, and results were effectively determined by how fast the drivers drove on the generally narrow [[forest road]]s.
Since 1990, many of these events have been held during [[daylight]] [[hour]]s – making the [[competition]] more attractive to [[Spectator sport|spectators]].
